value.value: Adult fruitless neuron of the female aSP-g cluster belonging to a morphological subtype with dendritic arborization between the aSP-g1 and aSP-g3 groups on the anterior-posterior axis (Taisz et al., 2023). It is a lateral horn neuron that fasciculates with the AD1 primary neurite tract (Schlegel et al., 2021). It has a greater proportion of its dendritic arbor in the lateral horn than other female aSP-g neurons (Taisz et al., 2023). These cells receive input from projection neurons that receive input in antennal lobe glomerulus DA1 and they respond to the male sex pheromone cVA (Kohl et al., 2013; Taisz et al., 2023). There are around 3-5 of these cells per hemisphere (Taisz et al., 2023).
